# CSE Tracker — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Then fill in the values below.
# NEVER commit .env to version control (it's listed in .gitignore).
#
# For GitHub Actions, add these as repository secrets at:
#   Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Google Gemini API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here


# ── Telegram Bot ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Create a bot via @BotFather on Telegram → copy the bot token.
# 2. Add the bot to your target channel/group as an admin.
# 3. Get your chat ID:
#    - For a group: Send a message, then visit:
#      https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/getUpdates
#      Look for "chat": {"id": -100XXXXXXXXXX, ...}
#    - For a private channel: Use a bot like @userinfobot
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456789:ABCDefGhIJKlmNoPQRsTUVwxYZ
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=-1001234567890
